WEBVTT

00:07.790 --> 00:08.620
[Goose honks]

00:08.820 --> 00:10.970
♪

00:11.170 --> 00:13.280
Did you hear any of those rumors
about a list?

00:13.480 --> 00:15.280
Hank: Yeah,
I'm not making a list.

00:15.480 --> 00:17.630
It's this guy Dickie Pope.

00:17.830 --> 00:19.280
He's a real killer.

00:19.480 --> 00:22.240
Did you write that
recommendation for my daughter?

00:22.440 --> 00:23.720
I will.

00:23.920 --> 00:25.940
Don't write
the recommendation.

00:26.140 --> 00:29.080
I'm going to New York to
interview at the Arlyle School.

00:29.280 --> 00:31.300
Hank: My father's retirement
is gonna upset

00:31.500 --> 00:33.820
this very delicate balance
that we've achieved.

00:34.020 --> 00:36.070
He left,
and we don't speak.

00:43.780 --> 00:45.270
Hey. I got you--

00:45.470 --> 00:46.650
Oh, thank you.

00:53.870 --> 00:55.540
You're going to do great.

00:55.740 --> 00:56.790
They're going to love you...

00:58.440 --> 01:00.060
...and you're going to get
what you need

01:00.260 --> 01:01.540
to bring back to the principal,

01:01.740 --> 01:04.420
and he's going to have to
take you seriously.

01:04.620 --> 01:05.720
Yeah.

01:05.920 --> 01:07.890
I know.

01:11.680 --> 01:12.900
Is there something else?

01:13.100 --> 01:15.170
I think I'm worried about you.

01:15.370 --> 01:16.300
Really?

01:16.500 --> 01:17.300
Yeah.

01:17.500 --> 01:18.120
[car approaching]

01:19.680 --> 01:22.040
You've been a bit more...

01:22.240 --> 01:23.740
Hank-like than usual.

01:23.940 --> 01:25.350
[chuckles]

01:25.550 --> 01:27.130
Have I?

01:27.330 --> 01:29.310
Yeah.

01:29.510 --> 01:31.610
I don't know.

01:33.350 --> 01:34.320
I got it, I got it.

01:34.520 --> 01:35.180
Okay.

01:42.010 --> 01:42.850
Okay. Bye.

01:43.050 --> 01:44.150
Bye.

01:44.350 --> 01:45.930
See you in a couple of days.

01:50.410 --> 01:52.630
I have this weird feeling
you're going to end up in jail.

01:55.330 --> 01:56.940
Or the hospital?

01:58.030 --> 02:02.030
[♪♪]

02:25.490 --> 02:27.970
[♪♪]

02:31.540 --> 02:32.670
[geese honking overhead]

02:40.290 --> 02:41.770
[Chandler]
You know how they figure out

02:41.970 --> 02:43.160
which one leads?

02:44.590 --> 02:45.560
[student] I don't know.

02:45.760 --> 02:47.130
Seniority?

02:47.330 --> 02:48.260
Experience?

02:48.460 --> 02:49.870
It's hardest to lead

02:50.070 --> 02:51.990
because they get
all the wind resistance...

02:53.950 --> 02:57.000
but one goose will always
bear the burden.

02:58.220 --> 03:00.620
Each bird,
as it flaps its wings,

03:00.820 --> 03:03.360
is creating lift
for their fellow birds,

03:03.560 --> 03:05.360
except for the leader out front,

03:05.560 --> 03:07.710
always hardest on the leader.

03:07.910 --> 03:09.280
What if the leader leads them

03:09.480 --> 03:11.460
into a jet engine?

03:11.660 --> 03:12.890
That does happen.

03:13.090 --> 03:14.760
Often, people die, too,
at least,

03:14.960 --> 03:16.020
so it's even.

03:18.240 --> 03:20.160
[♪♪]

03:20.360 --> 03:21.810
[geese honking overhead]

03:25.240 --> 03:28.940
[♪♪]

03:52.010 --> 03:52.800
[knocking on door]

03:53.000 --> 03:53.760
Mr. Devereaux?

03:53.960 --> 03:55.330
I apologize.

03:55.530 --> 03:55.980
He'll be ready
in just a few more minutes.

03:56.180 --> 03:57.060
Oh, thank you.

04:01.240 --> 04:02.060
Hank!

04:04.410 --> 04:06.470
I'm President Dickie Pope.

04:06.670 --> 04:08.600
We've met four times.

04:08.800 --> 04:09.640
I remember.

04:09.840 --> 04:11.860
I remember, too.

04:12.060 --> 04:13.470
Please sit down,

04:13.670 --> 04:14.650
if you want.

04:14.850 --> 04:16.690
I'm going to sit down.

04:21.780 --> 04:22.790
So, are you hungry?

04:22.990 --> 04:25.360
Would you like
something to eat?

04:25.560 --> 04:27.450
Uh, I'll see the menu.

04:27.640 --> 04:28.490
Joke.

04:28.690 --> 04:29.880
Good.

04:30.080 --> 04:31.930
Hank, keep that sense of humor.

04:32.130 --> 04:33.670
It's going to come in handy.

04:33.870 --> 04:35.450
Hank, you are
the only department head

04:35.650 --> 04:38.150
who has not submitted a list
of faculty to cut.

04:38.350 --> 04:40.680
In that way, I'm outstanding.

04:40.880 --> 04:42.160
You are outstanding, Professor.

04:42.350 --> 04:44.110
You are
an accomplished professor,

04:44.310 --> 04:46.030
and a very well-regarded
novelist.

04:46.230 --> 04:48.110
I have your book...

04:53.070 --> 04:54.120
It's not there.

04:54.320 --> 04:55.290
Yeah, that's been happening.

04:55.550 --> 04:57.430
It's been disappearing
from the shelves

04:57.630 --> 04:59.220
of private collections
all around the country,

04:59.420 --> 05:01.570
only to reappear later
in a field,

05:01.770 --> 05:05.180
claiming
an extraordinary experience.

05:05.380 --> 05:07.300
Why haven't you
submitted a list?

05:08.690 --> 05:10.710
No one reason.

05:10.910 --> 05:12.360
Please elaborate.

05:12.560 --> 05:13.570
Can't.

05:13.830 --> 05:16.620
There's no reason
that I can think of.

05:16.820 --> 05:19.930
Granted, I haven't
given it a thought.

05:20.130 --> 05:22.410
You are missing an opportunity.

05:22.610 --> 05:23.720
This would be the first time.

05:23.920 --> 05:24.980
As you are aware,

05:25.180 --> 05:26.370
it is virtually impossible

05:26.570 --> 05:28.590
to fire a tenured professor
for cause.

05:28.790 --> 05:29.800
[faintly] Yeah.

05:30.020 --> 05:31.120
You are saddled
with your department,

05:31.320 --> 05:33.550
the good and the bad.

05:33.750 --> 05:36.510
These budget cuts
present an opportunity

05:36.710 --> 05:37.950
to remove the ones--

05:38.150 --> 05:39.780
and I'm sure you know
who they are already--

05:39.980 --> 05:41.560
who shouldn't be here.

05:41.760 --> 05:46.090
You will reshape
your department.

05:46.290 --> 05:48.530
Everybody will be better off.

05:48.730 --> 05:50.310
You will bring in
new professors in the future,

05:50.510 --> 05:53.180
ones you have chosen yourself.

05:53.380 --> 05:54.970
Yeah, but
how could we afford that?

05:55.170 --> 05:56.400
Won't much of the money

05:56.600 --> 06:00.410
be going to this
Technical Careers Complex?

06:00.610 --> 06:02.370
There seems to be
a misunderstanding here.

06:02.570 --> 06:04.590
The university
is not spending a dime

06:04.790 --> 06:05.590
on the Epstein Center.

06:05.790 --> 06:07.150
Epstein is.

06:07.350 --> 06:08.630
It's a gift.

06:08.830 --> 06:10.160
He paid for the building,

06:10.360 --> 06:11.770
the staff, and maintenance

06:11.970 --> 06:14.290
for 10 years.

06:14.490 --> 06:17.210
He's coming to
the groundbreaking tomorrow...

06:17.410 --> 06:19.430
[Hank, thinking]
<i>I'll bet the tiny tree business</i>

06:19.630 --> 06:21.820
<i>is hard to break into.</i>

06:22.020 --> 06:24.610
<i>I mean, it's not worth building</i>
<i>a machine to make 'em.</i>

06:24.810 --> 06:26.130
<i>It's got to be by hand,</i>

06:26.330 --> 06:27.260
<i>or maybe they just, you know,</i>

06:27.460 --> 06:29.350
<i>cut down</i>
<i>a tiny forest somewhere,</i>

06:29.550 --> 06:30.820
<i>completely ignoring</i>

06:31.170 --> 06:34.960
<i>what must be a sizeable crowd</i>
<i>of Smurf protesters.</i>

06:35.160 --> 06:36.790
Yeah.

06:36.990 --> 06:38.320
Look, nothing about

06:38.510 --> 06:41.750
the Jeffrey Epstein
Technical Careers Center

06:41.950 --> 06:42.880
looks good.

06:44.620 --> 06:46.670
You're referring to the name.

06:46.870 --> 06:48.280
People are familiar
with the many instances

06:48.480 --> 06:50.110
in which young women
were attacked

06:50.310 --> 06:53.070
by a technical careers center.

06:53.270 --> 06:55.290
Different Jeffrey Epstein.

06:55.490 --> 06:58.160
This one made
two billion on air fryers.

06:58.360 --> 06:59.860
We're adding a "Q".

07:00.060 --> 07:02.340
Queer fryers?

07:02.540 --> 07:04.470
It will be
the Jeffrey Q. Epstein Center.

07:04.670 --> 07:06.690
What's his middle name?

07:06.890 --> 07:07.740
He doesn't have one.

07:07.940 --> 07:09.250
He's not thrilled with the "Q".

07:11.730 --> 07:14.440
The legislature is cutting
our budget by 23%.

07:14.640 --> 07:16.880
Please make a list
so we are prepared.

07:17.070 --> 07:18.830
I've gotten this far
without making a list.

07:19.030 --> 07:21.660
If I were to start now,
I'd feel like a quitter.

07:21.860 --> 07:22.520
No.

07:26.090 --> 07:28.280
Uh, look, Dickie, um...

07:28.480 --> 07:31.370
you're new around here.

07:31.570 --> 07:33.980
Every year,
those geniuses in Harrisburg,

07:34.180 --> 07:35.150
they threaten cuts,

07:35.350 --> 07:37.420
and every year, they don't,

07:37.620 --> 07:39.290
because, as we've established,

07:39.490 --> 07:41.030
they don't like
not looking good.

07:41.230 --> 07:42.940
This year is different.

07:43.140 --> 07:45.560
Because of how time works?

07:45.760 --> 07:48.120
They likely will give us
what we ask for...

07:48.320 --> 07:49.950
but I'm not asking for it.

07:50.150 --> 07:51.950
All my predecessors

07:52.150 --> 07:55.520
have begged year after year
for more money.

07:55.720 --> 07:58.000
I'm not going to do that.

07:58.200 --> 08:00.090
I'm lobbying for less money.

08:00.290 --> 08:01.220
The school's too fat.

08:01.420 --> 08:02.870
[♪♪]

08:05.390 --> 08:09.480
[♪♪]

08:16.060 --> 08:17.490
[Hank] Shut the door, please.

08:21.970 --> 08:23.590
I talked to Dickie Pope.

08:23.790 --> 08:25.070
What? When?

08:25.270 --> 08:26.290
Earlier today.

08:26.490 --> 08:27.510
He called me into his office.

08:27.710 --> 08:28.420
He wanted to talk to me.

08:29.940 --> 08:30.910
To talk about the cuts?

08:31.110 --> 08:32.520
And you went?

08:32.720 --> 08:34.000
Did you give him a list?

08:34.200 --> 08:35.820
Do you think
I would make a list?

08:36.020 --> 08:37.560
Tell me you didn't give him
a list.

08:37.760 --> 08:39.390
If I told you
I didn't give him a list,

08:39.590 --> 08:40.700
would you believe me?

08:40.900 --> 08:41.960
No.

08:42.160 --> 08:43.660
Then I'm not telling you.

08:43.860 --> 08:46.790
You went to see Dickie Pope
without talking to us first?

08:46.990 --> 08:48.360
It wouldn't have
made a difference, Paul.

08:48.560 --> 08:50.660
Wouldn't have made
a difference?

08:50.860 --> 08:52.580
Screw you!

08:52.780 --> 08:54.190
We could have had
a strategy session,

08:54.390 --> 08:55.630
brought Leslie in.

08:55.830 --> 08:57.980
Whew! I missed out
on a strategy session

08:58.180 --> 08:59.190
with Leslie.

08:59.390 --> 09:00.810
You see us out there, right?

09:01.000 --> 09:03.810
You see that we think
we can have a voice in this,

09:04.010 --> 09:05.640
that we need to.

09:05.840 --> 09:07.810
You're the one without a voice.

09:08.010 --> 09:12.690
You just decided
it doesn't matter what we think.

09:12.890 --> 09:14.340
[ <i>"I Just Got The News"</i>
by The Gentrys playing]

09:14.540 --> 09:16.210
[Paul's voice fading out]
You see, that's the exact reason

09:16.410 --> 09:18.260
collective action fails...

09:18.460 --> 09:19.610
[music track drowning out Paul]

09:19.810 --> 09:21.650
...because when you undermine
the union,

09:21.850 --> 09:22.780
you're undermining all of us!

09:22.980 --> 09:26.400
♪ What am I gonna do?

09:26.600 --> 09:30.660
♪ No matter what I do

09:30.860 --> 09:34.660
♪ But I've done
everything I can... ♪

09:56.940 --> 09:59.070
[car horns honking,
city traffic roaring]

10:01.730 --> 10:05.080
[♪♪]

10:18.180 --> 10:19.010
Lily!

10:19.210 --> 10:20.700
Tom.

10:22.970 --> 10:24.020
Hi!

10:24.220 --> 10:24.980
Are you kidding me?

10:25.180 --> 10:26.020
Who are you?

10:26.220 --> 10:26.980
Well, hi.

10:27.180 --> 10:29.420
[chuckling]

10:29.610 --> 10:31.540
- Great to see you.
- You too.

10:33.280 --> 10:34.380
So the students
don't have any textbooks?

10:34.580 --> 10:35.810
No, it's all digital.

10:36.010 --> 10:37.160
They have access
to whatever they need on them

10:37.360 --> 10:38.950
at any time.

10:39.150 --> 10:41.120
It means more personal
connections between students,

10:41.320 --> 10:42.990
and between teachers
and students.

10:43.190 --> 10:44.210
Dina!

10:44.410 --> 10:45.690
Way to crush it
at the regionals.

10:45.890 --> 10:47.130
Excellent work.

10:47.330 --> 10:48.260
Regional physics challenge.

10:48.460 --> 10:51.260
She is amazing.

10:51.460 --> 10:52.740
The kids look too happy.

10:52.940 --> 10:54.180
Yeah, I know,
it takes some getting used to,

10:54.380 --> 10:56.180
but trust me,
this is not all for show.

10:56.380 --> 10:57.400
Every choice we make

10:57.600 --> 11:00.710
has been backed
by lots of research.

11:00.910 --> 11:02.100
What?

11:02.300 --> 11:03.430
No, I'm just...

11:03.630 --> 11:04.930
I'm just trying to square
this new Tom

11:05.130 --> 11:06.710
with the one
who, um, quit his job

11:06.910 --> 11:08.190
by telling his boss
to get cancer.

11:08.390 --> 11:09.320
Ah.

11:09.520 --> 11:10.800
That was a long time ago.

11:11.000 --> 11:12.070
Plus, I heard
he actually did die of cancer...

11:12.270 --> 11:13.590
Oh!

11:13.790 --> 11:14.460
...so I have to be
very careful with my power.

11:14.660 --> 11:16.900
No... [laughing]

11:17.100 --> 11:19.160
This administration
is crazy supportive,

11:19.360 --> 11:21.030
they're open-minded.

11:21.230 --> 11:22.380
You're going to be walking into
a very smoothly-run ecosystem--

11:22.580 --> 11:23.730
If...
If I get this job.

11:23.930 --> 11:24.950
Sure, "if", "if".

11:25.150 --> 11:26.390
I mean, no pressure,

11:26.580 --> 11:27.930
but you'd better
nail this interview.

11:28.130 --> 11:29.430
Do you have any idea
how many hand jobs I had to give

11:29.630 --> 11:30.520
to get you this meeting?

11:30.720 --> 11:31.480
Three.

11:31.680 --> 11:32.740
Eight.

11:32.940 --> 11:33.740
They were all on myself,
to set the mood,

11:33.940 --> 11:35.690
but still, I am exhausted.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.750
I should take a video
of myself right here

11:38.950 --> 11:40.360
and send it to my principal.

11:40.560 --> 11:41.920
Guy would crap his pants.

11:42.120 --> 11:43.140
Yeah?

11:43.340 --> 11:44.750
You ready
to burn that bridge?

11:44.950 --> 11:47.620
Oh, I'm ready for him
to give me everything I want.

11:47.820 --> 11:49.100
What do you mean?
What do you want?

11:49.300 --> 11:50.980
Well, it's just, you know,
if I stayed in Railton,

11:51.170 --> 11:53.760
this interview could give me
some leverage.

11:53.960 --> 11:54.810
Leverage?

11:55.000 --> 11:57.160
Well, don't you want this job?

11:57.350 --> 11:58.290
Oh, well, yeah.

11:58.490 --> 12:01.290
I mean, yeah, but, um...

12:01.490 --> 12:03.030
I mean, if I'm honest,

12:03.230 --> 12:05.110
a move would be
really hard for me right now.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.120
Well, oh, my God.

12:08.320 --> 12:09.560
Oh, my God.

12:09.760 --> 12:10.690
- Lily!
- I'm sorry, Tom.

12:10.890 --> 12:12.120
I didn't think--

12:12.470 --> 12:13.740
If I had I seen you here
and how much you obviously care,

12:13.940 --> 12:14.930
then I wouldn't have--

12:15.130 --> 12:16.700
- [exhaling]
- Do you want me to go?

12:16.900 --> 12:18.960
You could say
that I got sick or died,

12:19.160 --> 12:20.790
or got...

12:20.990 --> 12:22.700
kidnapped by big city rats.

12:22.900 --> 12:23.960
You can't bail now!

12:24.160 --> 12:25.570
If you do,
I'll look like an idiot.

12:27.000 --> 12:28.930
Just go in there and be great.

12:29.130 --> 12:30.360
Well, no, no, don't be great.

12:30.560 --> 12:33.060
Just be... medium great.

12:33.260 --> 12:34.240
[whimpers]

12:34.440 --> 12:35.320
Can you be medium?

12:35.520 --> 12:36.500
Okay.

12:36.700 --> 12:38.060
[grunting]

12:42.060 --> 12:43.460
I know that you care about
those professors,

12:43.660 --> 12:45.680
despite the fact
that you would never admit that,

12:45.880 --> 12:47.550
but you complain
about these people all the time,

12:47.750 --> 12:48.820
about their incompetence,

12:49.020 --> 12:50.300
and in the end,

12:50.490 --> 12:53.390
don't you have to think
about the students?

12:53.580 --> 12:54.680
That's not the point.

12:56.470 --> 12:57.420
Oh, I'm having a hard time

12:57.770 --> 12:59.300
figuring out
what the point is lately.

12:59.500 --> 13:02.220
<i>I have this weird feeling </i>
<i>you're going to end up in jail.</i>

13:02.420 --> 13:04.400
Or the hospital?

13:04.600 --> 13:05.180
[Tony] <i>In the hospital?</i>

13:05.380 --> 13:07.230
Or jail.

13:07.420 --> 13:08.660
I think
they're very different places.

13:08.860 --> 13:11.270
Yeah, so,
what's the common thread?

13:11.470 --> 13:12.840
I don't know, uh...

13:13.040 --> 13:14.060
Trouble?

13:14.260 --> 13:15.840
Loss of control?

13:16.040 --> 13:18.150
Yeah, that's not insight.

13:18.350 --> 13:19.500
All right.

13:19.700 --> 13:20.660
Let me think.
You punch.

13:21.840 --> 13:22.760
All right,
let's draw on philosophy.

13:22.960 --> 13:24.240
Let's articulate the question.

13:24.440 --> 13:26.720
Yeah.
Why is Lily upset with me?

13:26.920 --> 13:28.250
Well, I can't solve that
with philosophy.

13:28.450 --> 13:29.680
Here's something we can tackle,

13:29.880 --> 13:31.120
what's a good and moral way

13:31.320 --> 13:33.770
for you to handle
your current work crisis?

13:33.970 --> 13:35.210
How should you act?

13:35.410 --> 13:36.510
Do nothing.

13:36.720 --> 13:37.820
No, you act
according to your desire,

13:38.020 --> 13:39.000
unless you're a Buddhist,

13:39.200 --> 13:40.080
then you should desire nothing.

13:40.280 --> 13:41.740
That eliminates suffering.

13:41.940 --> 13:44.220
See, that's my problem
with Buddhism.

13:44.420 --> 13:46.090
Suffering,

13:46.290 --> 13:49.050
that's my sweet spot, right?

13:49.250 --> 13:51.180
At least I know I'm alive,
I'm feeling something.

13:51.380 --> 13:52.970
Huh.

13:53.170 --> 13:55.010
Maybe Lily wants you to feel
something more than suffering.

13:55.210 --> 13:56.490
Why would she want that?

13:56.690 --> 13:57.710
I don't know, you tell me.

13:57.910 --> 13:59.060
One word per punch.
Let it out.

13:59.260 --> 14:00.060
Because!

14:00.260 --> 14:01.110
It's!

14:01.300 --> 14:02.920
Boring!

14:04.270 --> 14:06.410
Because...

14:06.610 --> 14:08.230
she's bored with me.

14:12.800 --> 14:13.640
Finny.

14:13.840 --> 14:15.990
Chopping block.

14:16.190 --> 14:19.080
He teaches the fewest students
to the lowest result.

14:19.280 --> 14:21.080
High attrition rate, too.

14:21.280 --> 14:22.260
Gracie.

14:22.460 --> 14:23.130
Chopping block.

14:23.330 --> 14:24.520
She's a headache.

14:24.720 --> 14:26.740
Constantly filing grievances.

14:26.940 --> 14:29.090
Granted, she's correct,
but still.

14:29.290 --> 14:31.140
Emma?

14:31.330 --> 14:33.310
What she does
isn't even English.

14:33.510 --> 14:34.090
Chopping block.

14:34.290 --> 14:35.920
