25:39.000 --> 25:40.330
[goose honking]

25:40.520 --> 25:42.370
We are here at a groundbreaking

25:42.570 --> 25:43.940
for a building
that is being paid for

25:44.140 --> 25:45.810
by cutting faculty!

25:46.010 --> 25:48.730
I heard that
directly from the mouth

25:48.920 --> 25:51.640
of the reliable, honorable
other Jeffrey Epstein.

25:51.840 --> 25:53.600
No!
No, I say!

25:53.800 --> 25:55.340
It will not stand!

25:55.540 --> 25:56.560
- [goose honking]
- I will box

25:56.760 --> 25:58.170
one of Railton's beloved geese!

25:58.370 --> 26:00.820
I will box a goose a day

26:01.020 --> 26:04.570
until I get my budget
fully funded!

26:04.770 --> 26:05.960
I'll punch him
in the upper neck

26:06.160 --> 26:07.790
and I'll punch him
in the lower neck!

26:07.990 --> 26:10.620
The goose is mostly neck.

26:10.820 --> 26:12.710
- That idiot.
- [Dean Rose, over mic] <i>Okay!</i>

26:12.910 --> 26:14.050
- [Hank] I will box him, and...
<i>- Over here, please!</i>

26:14.250 --> 26:15.580
<i>Over here, please!</i>

26:15.780 --> 26:17.620
No cutting jobs!

26:17.820 --> 26:18.970
[chanting together]
No cutting jobs!

26:19.170 --> 26:20.190
No cutting jobs!

26:20.390 --> 26:21.980
Ladies and gentlemen,

26:22.180 --> 26:23.670
I'd like to...

26:23.870 --> 26:24.800
[chanting] No cutting jobs!

26:25.000 --> 26:26.150
Here, buddy.

26:26.350 --> 26:27.500
Let's get out of here.

26:27.700 --> 26:28.960
- All right.
- Come on, come on, come on.

26:29.160 --> 26:31.290
I'd like to start
tonight's ceremony with a poem

26:31.490 --> 26:33.470
by our very own Gracie Dubois!

26:33.660 --> 26:34.680
[chanting continues]
No cutting jobs!

26:34.880 --> 26:36.380
No cutting jobs!
No cutting jobs!

26:36.580 --> 26:38.380
Gracie Dubois, everyone.

26:38.580 --> 26:40.210
No cutting jobs!
No cutting jobs!

26:40.410 --> 26:41.780
Grace!

26:41.980 --> 26:42.510
No cutting jobs! No--

26:49.300 --> 26:50.830
You're going to love
this place.

26:51.030 --> 26:52.010
She should be here.

26:52.210 --> 26:53.660
I told her to meet us at 5:00.

26:53.860 --> 26:55.880
- Lily!
- Whoo-hoo!

26:56.080 --> 26:57.710
Aw, yeah!

26:57.910 --> 26:59.880
Oh, my god,
it's so good to see you.

27:00.080 --> 27:01.010
Oh, buddy.

27:01.210 --> 27:02.150
So? How'd it go?

27:02.350 --> 27:02.890
Did you get the gig?

27:03.090 --> 27:04.190
They loved her.

27:04.390 --> 27:05.410
Let's go look for apartments
right now.

27:05.610 --> 27:06.890
Oh, that sounds so fun.

27:07.090 --> 27:08.200
[Tom] It does sound fun.
Not going to happen.

27:08.400 --> 27:09.410
We were hoodwinked.

27:09.610 --> 27:10.850
The whole interview was a con.

27:11.050 --> 27:12.680
She leveraged us, Ash.

27:12.880 --> 27:14.290
Leverage for what?

27:14.490 --> 27:15.930
Her cutthroat
public school job.

27:17.370 --> 27:19.120
You scammer!

27:19.320 --> 27:20.380
So you just flash your tits
at the old flame,

27:20.580 --> 27:21.300
and he comes running.

27:21.500 --> 27:22.650
I did not flash my tits.

27:22.840 --> 27:23.520
I did not run.

27:23.710 --> 27:24.470
You two never change.

27:24.670 --> 27:25.950
It was just--

27:26.150 --> 27:27.260
You know, it was just business.

27:27.460 --> 27:28.390
I do feel bad, though.

27:28.590 --> 27:30.520
Well, you shouldn't.

27:30.720 --> 27:32.090
Uh, since we seem to be
truth-telling,

27:32.290 --> 27:33.130
I haven't had a drink yet,

27:33.330 --> 27:36.090
but, um, the job wasn't, uh,

27:36.290 --> 27:38.700
how shall we say, really...
available.

27:38.900 --> 27:40.140
What do you mean?

27:40.340 --> 27:41.530
Well, you didn't hear this
from me,

27:41.730 --> 27:42.930
and I didn't want
to bum you out,

27:43.130 --> 27:44.510
but there was
this huge meeting last week

27:44.710 --> 27:45.930
about how they wanted to
re-commit to diversity hiring,

27:46.130 --> 27:47.280
and, so...

27:47.480 --> 27:49.720
- Oh.
- Yeah.

27:49.920 --> 27:50.720
Okay.

27:50.920 --> 27:51.720
Yeah, I get that.

27:51.920 --> 27:53.060
I really thought

27:53.320 --> 27:54.150
we were going to have her
back in New York,

27:54.350 --> 27:56.510
but, well, that's our Lily,

27:56.700 --> 27:58.330
always playing us.

27:58.530 --> 27:59.900
What? That's not me,
I don't play people.

28:00.100 --> 28:02.340
Oh, shut up and get me a drink.

28:02.540 --> 28:04.160
[Tom] Yes. Uh, drinks!

28:04.360 --> 28:05.780
Are you thinking of
getting some food, gentlemen?

28:05.970 --> 28:07.990
The drink of the day
is a Mikhail Gorbachev.

28:08.190 --> 28:09.450
What's that?

28:09.650 --> 28:11.170
It's a Moscow Mule,
served in a glass... nost.

28:11.370 --> 28:12.260
[scoffs, snorting]

28:12.460 --> 28:13.520
[groans]

28:13.720 --> 28:15.600
Uh, I'll leave you guys to it.

28:17.470 --> 28:18.090
They changed the menu,

28:18.290 --> 28:20.750
without warning.

28:20.950 --> 28:22.230
I didn't come this restaurant.

28:22.430 --> 28:24.140
I came to the one
that has the shrimp I like.

28:24.340 --> 28:25.580
[Hank whispers]
Bait and switch.

28:25.780 --> 28:27.060
I'm ordering off the old menu.

28:27.260 --> 28:28.800
From memory?

28:29.000 --> 28:31.240
I believe death
will come quickly for me.

28:31.430 --> 28:33.540
Uh, change of subject?

28:33.740 --> 28:34.500
Not because I want it to,

28:34.700 --> 28:35.890
but because

28:36.090 --> 28:37.460
most of the deepest
experiences of my life

28:37.660 --> 28:39.030
have been unexpected.

28:39.230 --> 28:41.590
The important thing
is we must prepare to transcend.

28:41.790 --> 28:42.900
Did something happen?

28:43.100 --> 28:43.900
My ex got remarried.

28:44.100 --> 28:44.990
That was years ago.

28:45.190 --> 28:45.990
The other one.

28:46.190 --> 28:47.250
We had an implicit promise

28:47.450 --> 28:48.630
that we would get back together

28:48.900 --> 28:50.600
if we were both still single
when we turned 70.

28:50.800 --> 28:51.910
I had no intention
of keeping it.

28:52.110 --> 28:53.170
I hate her, but still.

28:53.370 --> 28:54.740
Pay attention,
I'm getting somewhere.

28:54.940 --> 28:56.520
You have my attention.

28:56.720 --> 28:59.000
I've decided fornication

28:59.200 --> 29:00.440
may no longer be
the primary goal.

29:00.640 --> 29:02.400
It may, in fact,
be counterproductive.

29:02.600 --> 29:04.220
You have half my attention.

29:04.420 --> 29:06.490
The body deteriorates.

29:06.690 --> 29:08.930
It reminds us that time,

29:09.120 --> 29:12.580
although an illusion,
is a robust one.

29:12.780 --> 29:14.060
All we can do is watch.

29:14.260 --> 29:17.020
First go the knees,
then the spleen,

29:17.220 --> 29:20.150
then the rest of the body,
the whole thing,

29:20.350 --> 29:22.980
until we're just
a ghost in the machine,

29:23.180 --> 29:24.810
then no machine.

29:25.010 --> 29:27.590
Casey Jones without a train.

29:29.370 --> 29:30.990
[Paul] There he is,

29:31.190 --> 29:32.820
the bird boxer.

29:33.020 --> 29:34.430
Quite a prank.

29:34.630 --> 29:36.000
Say thank you.
Look--

29:36.200 --> 29:37.300
You knew what we were planning.

29:37.500 --> 29:38.390
Said he didn't want
any part of it.

29:38.590 --> 29:39.780
I--

29:39.980 --> 29:42.310
Then you go and upstage
the entire thing.

29:42.510 --> 29:43.790
The whole goddamn thing.

29:43.990 --> 29:44.790
Shut up, Billie.

29:44.990 --> 29:46.440
The whole goddamn thing.

29:46.640 --> 29:49.440
In my defense,
the goose was an asshole.

29:49.640 --> 29:51.050
[Paul] In your defense,

29:51.250 --> 29:53.840
it was a pretty big F-U
to the administration

29:54.040 --> 29:56.090
for a guy who says
he's not a union man.

29:58.180 --> 30:00.530
Come join us, jackass.

30:04.670 --> 30:06.160
[rapping fingers on tabletop]

30:06.360 --> 30:07.200
[laughing]

30:07.400 --> 30:08.620
No, listen, listen, listen.

30:08.810 --> 30:11.290
So, there wasn't a school system
in the country

30:11.490 --> 30:12.900
that wasn't
completely uprooted by Covid,

30:13.100 --> 30:14.420
but even, you know,

30:14.630 --> 30:16.910
with all the staff turnover
and the budget fights,

30:17.110 --> 30:18.260
and all the other crap
that goes along with it,

30:18.450 --> 30:19.470
I've got to say
we fared pretty well.

30:19.670 --> 30:20.740
[Tom] Pretty well?

30:20.940 --> 30:22.300
Top 20 charter school
in the city.

30:22.500 --> 30:24.830
Top 15, depending on
which report you read.

30:25.030 --> 30:26.700
Last week, I cleaned up
a student's piss

30:26.900 --> 30:28.730
because my janitor
felt it was beneath him.

30:31.040 --> 30:32.010
Gross.

30:32.210 --> 30:33.570
[chuckles]

30:35.090 --> 30:36.230
You know what it is?

30:36.430 --> 30:38.320
This Arlyle job,

30:38.520 --> 30:40.760
it, like,
got my engine running again.

30:40.960 --> 30:42.670
I'm listening to you
talk about your schools

30:42.870 --> 30:44.280
and your careers,

30:44.480 --> 30:47.370
and that's the reason
that we went to grad school

30:47.570 --> 30:48.500
in the first place.

30:48.700 --> 30:50.420
That was always the dream,

30:50.620 --> 30:52.900
and I just... miss it.

30:53.100 --> 30:54.500
Miss it?

30:54.720 --> 30:56.820
I'm sure you talk like this
at home all the time, no?

30:57.020 --> 30:58.600
[chuckles ruefully]

30:58.800 --> 31:00.210
Oh, my God.

31:00.410 --> 31:01.340
Do you know

31:01.540 --> 31:02.910
Hank just publicly announced

31:03.110 --> 31:05.130
that all the students
and teachers at Railton

31:05.330 --> 31:07.730
should resign themselves
to their mediocrity.

31:09.340 --> 31:10.700
- Oh, shit.
- Oh...

31:10.900 --> 31:11.690
Yeah.

31:11.910 --> 31:14.700
I mean, he was kidding, but...

31:14.900 --> 31:16.360
no, he wasn't.

31:16.560 --> 31:17.270
[laughing and chatting]

31:17.470 --> 31:18.270
Whoa!

31:18.470 --> 31:20.620
Hey!

31:20.820 --> 31:21.800
What's everybody else having?

31:22.000 --> 31:23.280
- [laughing]
- That's a good one...

31:23.480 --> 31:25.580
- [groaning and bantering]
- Mean lady...

31:25.780 --> 31:27.540
- Let's do this.
- There we go.

31:27.740 --> 31:30.110
Uh, here is to Dickie Pope

31:30.310 --> 31:32.370
and the look on his face.

31:32.570 --> 31:33.710
- Oh, wow.
- [all clinking glasses]

31:36.110 --> 31:37.940
Gracie, your poem, your ode.

31:38.140 --> 31:39.510
You never had a chance
to read it.

31:39.710 --> 31:40.510
[Billie] Come on,
we want to hear it.

31:40.710 --> 31:41.770
[all agreeing]
Come on!

31:41.970 --> 31:43.210
- Go ahead.
- Yeah!

31:43.410 --> 31:46.600
No, I think the focus
is split at the moment.

31:46.800 --> 31:47.930
- No, we wanna hear it.
- Come on.

31:48.130 --> 31:49.480
Trust us,
this will never happen again,

31:49.680 --> 31:50.520
- so...
- [laughter]

31:50.720 --> 31:52.000
We're happy to hear it.

31:52.200 --> 31:52.950
Go for it.

31:54.300 --> 31:56.000
[tapping glass]

32:01.520 --> 32:05.750
"We dipped our palms
in chalk to

32:05.950 --> 32:08.760
"keep our hands
from letting go,

32:08.960 --> 32:10.840
and..."

32:15.490 --> 32:16.680
Go on, Gracie.

32:16.880 --> 32:19.160
This is as quiet
as the bar's going to get.

32:19.360 --> 32:20.250
No, I--

32:20.450 --> 32:21.380
Yeah, finish the poem.

32:21.580 --> 32:23.340
- Yeah, come on.
- Finish it.

32:23.540 --> 32:24.850
That's the end.

32:26.680 --> 32:28.910
So read the beginning.

32:29.110 --> 32:32.960
No, that...
That was the...

32:33.150 --> 32:35.440
Well, perhaps
you can read it again

32:35.640 --> 32:37.570
now that we know more
about what to expect.

32:37.770 --> 32:39.830
You did end it with an "and".

32:40.030 --> 32:43.050
[♪♪]

32:43.250 --> 32:44.360
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

32:44.560 --> 32:45.270
[Hank, voicemail message]
<i>Hey, Lil,</i>

32:45.470 --> 32:46.730
<i>uh, the weirdest thing,</i>

32:46.930 --> 32:48.540
<i>but, well, you don't</i>
<i>have to worry about me.</i>

32:48.740 --> 32:50.390
<i>I boxed this goose.</i>

32:50.590 --> 32:52.240
<i>He was--</i>

32:52.430 --> 32:53.440
<i>Well, he was being a jerk,</i>

32:53.660 --> 32:56.200
<i>and, well,</i>
<i>now the faculty like me?</i>

32:56.400 --> 32:57.280
<i>Um, okay.</i>

32:57.480 --> 32:58.150
<i>I'm sorry I keep missing you.</i>

32:58.350 --> 32:59.680
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

32:59.880 --> 33:00.770
[Lily, voicemail message]
<i>Um...</i>

33:00.960 --> 33:01.400
<i>please don't hurt any animals.</i>

33:01.600 --> 33:02.940
<i>I mean,</i>

33:03.140 --> 33:04.550
<i>I would have said something</i>
<i>before I left,</i>

33:04.750 --> 33:05.860
<i>but, um, [laughing],</i>

33:06.060 --> 33:07.820
<i>but, um, I thought you knew.</i>

33:08.020 --> 33:09.470
<i>So... okay.</i>

33:09.670 --> 33:11.040
<i>Um, so I'm going to take</i>
<i>the later train.</i>

33:11.240 --> 33:12.640
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

33:12.860 --> 33:14.690
[Hank, voicemail message]
<i>I missed your call again.</i>

33:14.890 --> 33:16.520
<i>Sorry, it's so noisy here.</i>

33:16.720 --> 33:18.780
<i>I'm out having drinks</i>
<i>with the department.</i>

33:18.980 --> 33:21.130
<i>Wish you were here!</i>

33:21.330 --> 33:24.140
<i>Uh... oh, why did you</i>
<i>change your train?</i>

33:24.340 --> 33:25.650
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

33:26.000 --> 33:27.230
[Lily, voicemail message]
<i>Hey, my phone was in my bag.</i>

33:27.430 --> 33:29.930
<i>I wish I saw your call.</i>

33:30.120 --> 33:31.880
<i>Not a great idea</i>
<i>to have drinks with them.</i>

33:32.080 --> 33:33.490
<i>You don't like them,</i>

33:33.690 --> 33:34.670
<i>so you should go home,</i>

33:34.870 --> 33:36.500
<i>and I will see you there.</i>

33:36.700 --> 33:37.660
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

33:37.880 --> 33:39.020
[Hank, voicemail message]
<i>Hey, uh,</i>

33:39.220 --> 33:42.290
<i>why are you</i>
<i>on a later train, huh?</i>

33:42.480 --> 33:44.940
<i>It doesn't... matter.</i>

33:45.140 --> 33:46.640
<i>It's just...</i>
<i>take whatever train.</i>

33:46.840 --> 33:48.290
<i>It's just, you know,</i>

33:48.490 --> 33:49.680
<i>there's a certain amount</i>
<i>of planning that goes into</i>

33:49.880 --> 33:51.160
<i>picking someone up</i>
<i>at the train station.</i>

33:51.360 --> 33:53.560
<i>It's just--</i>
<i>Anyway, that's... that's all.</i>

33:53.760 --> 33:55.520
[♪♪]

33:55.720 --> 33:57.130
[Teddy] Hey, Hank's on TV!

33:57.330 --> 33:59.120
Hey, Meg! Turn it up.

34:00.770 --> 34:01.610
<i>...Railton College,</i>

34:01.810 --> 34:03.310
<i>a fight broke out</i>

34:03.510 --> 34:04.520
<i>of a very unusual kind,</i>

34:04.720 --> 34:07.220
<i>but what started</i>
<i>as a silly prank</i>

34:07.420 --> 34:09.620
<i>ended up being</i>
<i>a serious challenge</i>

34:09.820 --> 34:10.860
<i>to the school brass.</i>

34:11.060 --> 34:12.360
<i>Now we are here</i>

34:12.560 --> 34:14.190
<i>at a groundbreaking</i>
<i>for a building</i>

34:14.390 --> 34:16.930
<i>that has been paid for</i>
<i>by cutting faculty!</i>

34:17.130 --> 34:19.500
[all cheering]
Yes! Yes! Yes!

34:19.700 --> 34:21.320
[Hank, on report] <i>...one of</i>
<i>Railton's beloved geese...</i>

34:21.520 --> 34:23.760
<i>I will box a goose a day</i>

34:23.960 --> 34:25.480
<i>until I get my budget</i>
<i>fully funded!</i>

34:25.680 --> 34:26.550
<i>Come on!</i>

34:26.750 --> 34:28.240
Did I say all that?

34:28.440 --> 34:29.330
I'm texting her now.

34:29.530 --> 34:31.030
- Texting who?
- Missy.

34:31.230 --> 34:32.460
- Missy who?
- The journalist.

34:38.110 --> 34:39.900
[cell phone ringing]

34:42.420 --> 34:43.960
[cell phone ringing]

34:44.150 --> 34:46.130
Hey! I was just
going to call you!

34:46.330 --> 34:47.440
<i>Why are you still there?</i>

34:47.640 --> 34:49.440
I'm having a drink
with Tom and Ashley.

34:49.640 --> 34:51.530
Who? W-What?

34:51.730 --> 34:53.010
I can't hear you.

34:53.210 --> 34:55.360
I am having a drink
with Tom and Ashley,

34:55.560 --> 34:57.710
so, um, I'm going to be
on a later train.

34:57.910 --> 34:58.920
I'll take a taxi.

35:00.270 --> 35:01.630
[Hank]
<i>Yeah, I'll come get you.</i>

35:01.820 --> 35:03.060
<i>Tell me when the train gets in.</i>

35:03.260 --> 35:04.310
Um, I don't know yet.

35:04.660 --> 35:06.190
[Hank] <i>Okay, well,</i>
<i>text me when you know.</i>

35:07.540 --> 35:09.200
<i>I'll pick you up.</i>

35:09.400 --> 35:12.020
<i>Just... Just tell me</i>
<i>when you get here.</i>

35:14.020 --> 35:16.940
<i>Lil?</i>
<i>Are you still there?</i>

35:18.680 --> 35:19.770
Um, yep.

35:19.970 --> 35:21.780
Yeah, yeah, I will text you.

35:21.980 --> 35:23.130
Okay, love you, love you.

35:23.320 --> 35:24.170
<i>Okay, uh, what?</i>

35:24.370 --> 35:24.940
Uh...

35:39.130 --> 35:40.880
The artwork
above the urinals is...

35:41.080 --> 35:43.410
I mean, masterpiece.

35:43.610 --> 35:45.760
I need another one of these.

35:45.960 --> 35:46.580
He still loves bathroom decor.

35:46.780 --> 35:48.540
He just kissed me.

35:48.740 --> 35:50.370
What?

35:50.570 --> 35:52.070
O-okay, hang on,

35:52.270 --> 35:53.940
that was... playing around,
that was not a real kiss.

35:54.140 --> 35:54.920
Tom...

35:55.120 --> 35:56.770
I thought we were flirting.

35:56.970 --> 35:57.770
Yeah, we were flirting,

35:57.970 --> 36:00.030
and then you ruined it.

36:00.230 --> 36:01.860
I was on the phone
with my husband.

36:02.060 --> 36:03.300
Right, I was making a joke.

36:03.500 --> 36:05.250
Who in their right mind
would kiss somebody

36:05.450 --> 36:06.510
that was on the phone
with their husband?

36:06.940 --> 36:08.250
- That was the joke--
- I'm married, you're married.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.560
Actually...

36:12.730 --> 36:14.000
We're separated.

36:14.200 --> 36:16.000
It's been a few months.
I was going to tell you.

36:16.200 --> 36:17.370
We tried.

36:17.570 --> 36:19.620
It was a lot of therapy,
not a lot of result.

36:19.820 --> 36:21.910
Well, I'm sorry...

36:23.440 --> 36:25.190
...but I still feel like
you're not hearing me.

36:25.390 --> 36:26.230
I mean, that?

36:26.430 --> 36:28.450
That... [sighs]

36:28.650 --> 36:30.570
...was not okay.

36:31.970 --> 36:34.490
I'm so sorry.

36:36.580 --> 36:37.930
Okay.

36:40.060 --> 36:40.510
This was so wonderful,
you guys--

36:40.710 --> 36:42.380
Oh, Lil...

36:42.580 --> 36:43.940
- -but I'm just
going to get going, so...

36:44.760 --> 36:47.300
...bye.

36:47.500 --> 36:48.810
[♪♪]

37:11.050 --> 37:13.500
All right.

37:13.700 --> 37:14.890
There you are,

37:15.090 --> 37:16.630
and this one is for Hank.

37:16.830 --> 37:18.240
Tell him it's on me.

37:18.440 --> 37:19.460
After taking away
your classes?

37:19.660 --> 37:20.280
No.

37:22.670 --> 37:23.680
What are you talking about?

37:23.880 --> 37:24.860
It was the administration.

37:25.050 --> 37:26.160
Mm-mm, it was him,

37:26.360 --> 37:27.530
and if tells you
that I asked him to,

37:27.730 --> 37:29.640
I'm telling you
that I was just spouting off.

37:29.840 --> 37:31.560
I didn't think
he'd go through with it.

37:31.760 --> 37:35.070
Who listens to somebody
ranting at 2:00 a.m.?

37:36.680 --> 37:38.730
[♪♪]

37:39.950 --> 37:42.220
Gracie, um, I've...

37:42.420 --> 37:45.700
I've never been a fan
of minimalist poetry,

37:45.900 --> 37:47.970
but I gotta say--

37:48.160 --> 37:49.530
You are not getting
your parking space back.

37:49.730 --> 37:50.440
No, no...

37:52.530 --> 37:53.930
- Good to go?
- Yeah, let's go.

37:54.130 --> 37:54.930
Oh, hey, Hank, here you go.

37:55.130 --> 37:56.280
- No, no, I'm fine.
- No?

37:56.480 --> 37:57.240
Yeah, we're done.

37:57.440 --> 37:58.110
Hey, guys,

37:58.310 --> 37:59.320
the conquering hero here

37:59.520 --> 38:00.630
- has to go home.
- No, no...

38:00.830 --> 38:02.370
No!

38:02.570 --> 38:03.680
- I'm not a hero--
- [all groaning in protest]

38:03.880 --> 38:04.940
- I'm not a hero.
- We're done.

38:05.140 --> 38:06.070
- Yeah...
- We're done here.

38:06.270 --> 38:07.420
We are done.

38:07.620 --> 38:08.680
Yeah, right,
we're done here, we're done.

38:08.880 --> 38:10.600
We're done here!

38:10.800 --> 38:12.290
- No, we're not done.
- Okay.

38:12.490 --> 38:13.600
You're, uh...

38:13.800 --> 38:15.120
- This is the guy from, uh...
- Yes.

38:15.320 --> 38:16.340
You think
you're pretty funny, huh?

38:16.540 --> 38:18.560
Professor A-hole.

38:18.760 --> 38:19.520
[Billie laughing]
Professor A-hole.

38:19.720 --> 38:20.560
I like that.

38:20.760 --> 38:22.090
Come on, let's--

38:22.290 --> 38:23.610
Geese have feelings, too,
all right? Just like us.

38:23.810 --> 38:25.960
Well, they have feelings,
but not like us.

38:26.160 --> 38:26.830
You think that's funny?

38:27.030 --> 38:28.000
Well, it's factual.

38:28.210 --> 38:29.350
It's a little funny,
don't you think?

38:29.550 --> 38:30.270
You know what I think
is funny--

38:30.470 --> 38:31.970
Whoa!
Whoa, hey!

38:32.170 --> 38:33.790
- What's going on?
- Whoa! [all shouting]

38:33.990 --> 38:35.060
[groaning] That's assault!

38:35.260 --> 38:36.320
You're going to jail!

38:36.520 --> 38:37.880
You're
going to jail!

38:38.080 --> 38:39.490
No one is going to jail!

38:41.010 --> 38:41.930
[Tony] God is dead,

38:42.130 --> 38:43.370
and we have killed him.

38:43.570 --> 38:44.530
Nietzsche's point

38:44.800 --> 38:45.500
isn't that we should live
in despair

38:45.700 --> 38:46.930
of ever finding meaning

38:47.150 --> 38:47.890
just because we've abandoned
the magical dogma

38:48.090 --> 38:49.640
of our particular age.

38:49.840 --> 38:50.770
Nietzsche wasn't a nihilist.

38:50.970 --> 38:53.120
"God is dead,

38:53.320 --> 38:55.470
and we have killed him."

38:55.670 --> 38:57.600
This is not cause for despair,
but celebration,

38:57.800 --> 39:00.120
for we have been liberated
by that murder

39:00.320 --> 39:01.520
to do what Nietzsche believed

39:01.720 --> 39:04.340
was the essential task
of all our lives...

39:06.730 --> 39:08.920
...to make meaning
from the world as we find it,

39:09.120 --> 39:10.870
not as we wish it to be.

39:11.070 --> 39:12.140
<i>[voicemail beeps]</i>

39:12.340 --> 39:14.360
[Lily] <i>It just got late,</i>

39:14.560 --> 39:16.180
<i>and so I decided</i>
<i>to stay in the city.</i>

39:16.380 --> 39:18.190
<i>Being in New York again,</i>

39:18.390 --> 39:19.430
<i>it feels like</i>
<i>I'm back in my 20s,</i>

39:19.630 --> 39:20.750
<i>like there was--</i>

39:20.950 --> 39:22.410
<i>there was so much possibility</i>

39:22.610 --> 39:25.320
<i>and surprises, you know.</i>

39:25.520 --> 39:26.930
<i>Anyway, I hope you went home,</i>

39:27.130 --> 39:28.240
<i>like I told you to,</i>

39:28.440 --> 39:30.850
<i>and are curled up</i>
<i>in a warm bed,</i>

39:31.050 --> 39:33.640
<i>and have managed</i>
<i>to stay out of the hospital.</i>

39:33.840 --> 39:34.640
<i>Ha, ha.</i>

39:34.840 --> 39:36.070
<i>All right, uh, good night.</i>

39:36.270 --> 39:37.420
[ <i>"In The Park"</i>
by The Jujus playing]

39:37.620 --> 39:39.820
♪ I... I can see

39:40.020 --> 39:41.600
♪ You and me

39:41.800 --> 39:43.420
♪ Walking hand in hand
through the park... ♪

39:45.600 --> 39:46.370
I'm gonna keep the clock.

39:46.570 --> 39:47.610
You want it in the house?

39:47.810 --> 39:48.610
I always thought of it as a
friend.

39:48.810 --> 39:50.220
[Grunts]

39:50.420 --> 39:52.050
You didn't mention a department
dinner party.

39:52.250 --> 39:54.270
I did not, I wanted you to come
over.

39:54.460 --> 39:55.880
[Screams]

39:56.080 --> 39:57.660
I'm being published in The
Atlantic.

39:57.860 --> 39:59.010
June, is it? Tony.

39:59.210 --> 40:00.100
Hi.

40:00.300 --> 40:00.620
You were flirting with my wife.

40:00.820 --> 40:02.060
Yeah...

40:02.260 --> 40:03.270
Is Hank mad about what happened?

40:03.470 --> 40:04.800
Nothing happened.

40:05.000 --> 40:05.840
[Phone vibrates]

40:06.040 --> 40:07.710
Tom, this isn't a good time.

40:07.910 --> 40:10.280
Hey Julie, it's mom.

40:10.480 --> 40:11.240
She's leaving us.

40:11.440 --> 40:14.320
♪♪

40:16.710 --> 40:20.670
[♪♪]
